      <h1 class='title'>Terrorism Act 2000</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 23 January 2003 vol 398 c25WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_25ws' title='Col. 25WS &mdash; HC Deb 23 January 2003 vol 398 c25WS' name='column_25ws' href='#column_25ws' rel='bookmark'>25WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0398P2_20030123_CWS_7'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-david-blunkett' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0398P2_20030123_CWS_7' title='Link to this speech by Mr David Blunkett' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-david-blunkett" title="Mr David Blunkett">The Secretary of State for the Home Department (Mr. David Blunkett)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">I am pleased to say that Lord Carlile of Berriew QC has completed the report on the operation of part VII of The <a href="/acts/terrorism-act-2000">Terrorism Act 2000</a>, which will be laid before the House today.</p>
        </blockquote>
